cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing a routing framework for Delay Tolerant Networks (DTNs) to achieve high throughput without external infrastructure. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper describes a routing framework that exploits the small world structure to entail only polylogarithmic storage and control overhead. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of probabilistic bounds on path length and delay. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper mentions sociability-based protocols and the small world structure of DTNs. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed routing framework through simulation-based evaluation.
